    "### 18.1 New engineered features\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Session intensity** — energy delivered per hour of charging (`energy_consumed_kwh / duration`), a\n",
    "  cleaner read on how \"hard\" a session is pulling than duration or energy alone.\n",
    "- **Rolling average station load** — each station's own trailing average load over its last 5\n",
    "  sessions, so we have a baseline to compare the current session against.\n",
    "- **Load delta** — how far the current session's station load sits from that rolling baseline.\n",
    "  Large positive deltas flag sessions arriving right as a station is spiking.\n",
    "- **Station utilization** — how many other sessions were actively charging at the same station at\n",
    "  the moment this one started, computed directly from the arrival/departure timestamps. This is\n",
    "  the closest proxy we have to the proposal's \"concurrent session count\" transformer-load signal."
