    "### 18.5 Outcome\n",
    "\n",
    "Here's the honest verdict, reading straight off the table above:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Linear Regression with the engineered features is the single best combination** — R² of 0.727,\n",
    "  the lowest MAE (3.90) and lowest RMSE (4.80) of all four options. It edges out plain Linear\n",
    "  Regression (R² 0.725) by a small but real margin.\n",
    "- The engineered features **help both models**, not just the Random Forest: Linear Regression\n",
    "  improves slightly (0.725 → 0.727) and the Random Forest improves more noticeably (0.708 → 0.716).\n",
    "- **Random Forest never catches Linear Regression**, with or without the new features — confirming\n",
    "  again that the relationships in this data are largely linear rather than needing a tree-based\n",
    "  model's flexibility.\n",
    "\n",
    "So the engineered features were worth building after all — not because they unlock a completely\n",
    "different model choice, but because they give a small, genuine lift to the model we'd already\n",
    "recommend. The updated recommendation: adopt **Linear Regression on the original + engineered\n",
    "feature set** as the production scoring model."
   ]
  },
